s to match the desired state described in a\n`,mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"p\",\"href\":\"/terraform/language\"},`Terraform configuration`),`. The\nTerraform binary includes commands and subcommands for a wide variety of infrastructure lifecycle management\nactions, but the following commands provide basic provisioning tasks: `),mdx(\"ul\",null,mdx(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"li\",\"id\":\"terrafrom-plan\",\"className\":\"__target-lic\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}),mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"li\",\"href\":\"#terrafrom-plan\",\"aria-label\":\"terrafrom plan permalink\",\"className\":\"__permalink-lic\"},mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"a\"},`terrafrom plan`)),` `),mdx(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"li\",\"id\":\"terraform-apply\",\"className\":\"__target-lic\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}),mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"li\",\"href\":\"#terraform-apply\",\"aria-label\":\"terraform apply permalink\",\"className\":\"__permalink-lic\"},mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"a\"},`terraform apply`))),mdx(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"li\",\"id\":\"terraform-destroy\",\"className\":\"__target-lic\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}),mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"li\",\"href\":\"#terraform-destroy\",\"aria-label\":\"terraform destroy permalink\",\"className\":\"__permalink-lic\"},mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"a\"},`terraform destroy`)),` `)),mdx(\"p\",null,`All of these commands require an `,mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"p\",\"href\":\"/terraform/cli/init\"},`initialized`),` working directory, and all of them act\nonly upon the currently selected `,mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"p\",\"href\":\"/terraform/cli/workspaces\"},`workspace`),`.`),mdx(\"h3\",{\"id\":\"plan\"},mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"h3\",\"className\":\"__permalink-h\",\"href\":\"#plan\",\"aria-label\":\"plan permalink\"},`\\xbb`),`Plan`),mdx(\"p\",null,`The `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform plan`),` command evaluates a Terraform configuration to determine\nthe desired state of all the resources it declares, then compares that desired\nstate to the real infrastructure objects being managed with the current working\ndirectory and workspace. It uses state data to determine which real objects\ncorrespond to which declared resources, and checks the current state of each\nresource using the relevant infrastructure provider's API.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`Once it has determined the difference between the current state and the desired\nstate, `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform plan`),` presents a description of the changes necessary to\nachieve the desired state. It `,mdx(\"em\",{parentName:\"p\"},`does not`),` perform any actual changes to real\nworld infrastructure objects; it only presents a plan for making changes.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`Plans are usually run to validate configuration changes and confirm that the\nresulting actions are as expected. However, `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform plan`),` can also save its\nplan as a runnable artifact, which `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform apply`),` can use to carry out those\nexact changes.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`For details, see `,mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"p\",\"href\":\"/terraform/cli/commands/plan\"},`the `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"a\"},`terraform plan`),` command`),`.`),mdx(\"h3\",{\"id\":\"apply\"},mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"h3\",\"className\":\"__permalink-h\",\"href\":\"#apply\",\"aria-label\":\"apply permalink\"},`\\xbb`),`Apply`),mdx(\"p\",null,`The `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform apply`),` command performs a plan just like `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform plan`),` does,\nbut then actually carries out the planned changes to each resource using the\nrelevant infrastructure provider's API. It asks for confirmation from the user\nbefore making any changes, unless it was explicitly told to skip approval.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`By default, `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform apply`),` performs a fresh plan right before applying\nchanges, and displays the plan to the user when asking for confirmation.\nHowever, it can also accept a plan file produced by `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform plan`),` in lieu of\nrunning a new plan. You can use this to reliably perform an exact set of\npre-approved changes, even if the configuration or the state of the real\ninfrastructure has changed in the minutes since the original plan was created.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`For details, see `,mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"p\",\"href\":\"/terraform/cli/commands/apply\"},`the `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"a\"},`terraform apply`),` command`),`.`),mdx(\"h3\",{\"id\":\"destroy\"},mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"h3\",\"className\":\"__permalink-h\",\"href\":\"#destroy\",\"aria-label\":\"destroy permalink\"},`\\xbb`),`Destroy`),mdx(\"p\",null,`The `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform destroy`),` command destroys all of the resources being managed by\nthe current working directory and workspace, using state data to determine which\nreal world objects correspond to managed resources. Like `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"p\"},`terraform apply`),`, it\nasks for confirmation before proceeding.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`A destroy behaves exactly like deleting every resource from the configuration\nand then running an apply, except that it doesn't require editing the\nconfiguration. This is more convenient if you intend to provision similar\nresources at a later date.`),mdx(\"p\",null,`For details, see `,mdx(\"a\",{parentName:\"p\",\"href\":\"/terraform/cli/commands/destroy\"},`the `,mdx(\"inlineCode\",{parentName:\"a\"},`terraform destroy`),` command`),`.`))};MDXContent.isMDXComponent=true;","scope":{"product":"terraform","version":"latest"}},"product":{"slug":"terraform","name":"Terraform","algoliaConfig":{"indexName":"product_TERRAFORM"},"alertBannerActive":true,"alertBanner":{"tag":"New","url":"https://www.hashicorp.com/blog/introducing-the-infrastructure-cloud","text":"Terraform Cloud is now HC